name: AuditFile
Description: OECD Standard Audit File: Standard Audit File - Taxation version 2.00 (Final version) OECD author TeA team last modified 17-09-2009

name: Header
Description: Holds general information about the file including the name of the software which produced it; the company on whose behalf the SAF-T is being submitted; and the selection criteria used. An extension point is provided to allow individual Revenue Bodies to  specify further relevant information to be supplied.

name: MasterFiles
Description: Holds standing data about general ledger account, suppliers, customers, products, etc.. An extension point is provided to allow Revenue Bodies to specify additional elements or structures such as tax rate tables.

name: Region
Description: Country specific code to indicate regions / provinces within the tax authority. Preferably described according to ISO 3166-2. Example: GB-KEN for Kent county in the United Kingdom.

name: Country
Description: Two-letter country code according to ISO 3166-1 alpha 2 standard. Example NL for the Netherlands.

name: AddressType
Description: Field to differentiate between multiple addresses. To indicate the type of address. Choose  from the predefined enumeration. (examples: StreetAddress PostalAddress, BillingAddress)

name: TaxIDStructure
Description: [Common to all SAFs] Tax information of a company.

name: TaxRegistrationNumber
Description: Unique number issued by a Revenue Body for use by the company.

name: TaxType
Description: For use where information reported in the SAF-T covers more than one type of tax regime: to identify the type of tax regime to which this entry relates.

name: TaxNumber
Description: The tax registration number for the particular tax regime referred to by TaxType, f.i. VAT-number

name: TaxAuthority
Description: Identification of the Revenue Body to which this TaxType refers.

name: TaxVerificationDate
Description: The date that the tax registration details referred to above were last checked.

name: AmountStructure
Description: [Common to all SAFs] A common structure used wherever an amount is required. Monetary amount with optional foreign currency exchange rate information.

name: Amount
Description: In the header's default currency.

name: CurrencyCode
Description: Three-letter currency code according to ISO 4217 standard. Example: EUR for the Euros or USD for American Dollars.

name: CurrencyAmount
Description: Amount in foreign currency.

name: ExchangeRate
Description: The exchange rate used. CurrencyAmount x ExchangeRate = Amount

Description: A formal sign or expression of greeting, expressed as text, that is appropriate for this person such as Right Honourable, Monsignor or Madam.

name: SelectionCriteriaStructure
Description: [Common to all SAFs] The selection criteria used to generate this Standard Auditfile

name: TaxReportingJurisdiction
Description: Identifies the tax jurisdiction for whose purpose the SAF has been created. Principally for use where a single Revenue body covers more than one territory.

name: CompanyEntity
Description: For use where data has been extracted from the full data set by reference to a specific corporate entity.

name: choice:SelectionStartDate-SelectionEndDate/PeriodStart-PeriodStartYear-PeriodEnd-PeriodEndYear
Description: Allows for a choice between selection on calendar dates and periods according to the accounting system, e.g. 1 to 12 for a 12-months accounting system.

name: DocumentType
Description: Type of documents selected. For use where the data has been restricted by reference to particular transaction types.

name: OtherCriteria
Description: Any other criteria used in selecting data. Individual Revenue Bodies may wish to draw up a list of other acceptable selection criteria for use within their jurisdiction

name: choice:SelectionStartDate-SelectionEndDate/PeriodStart-PeriodStartYear-PeriodEnd-PeriodEndYear

name: SelectionEndDate

name: PeriodEnd
